explicit blank; rejected if OS label is nonblank}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Use the same bracketed volume name each time you scan the same drive. For example, use [Backup-1]E:\\Music on Windows or [Backup-1]/mnt/e/Music on WSL/Linux for the same external drive. If no bracketed prefix is supplied, TLO resolves and uses the operating-system volume label when it can. The default labels New Volume and Local Disk are treated as blank rather than as useful unique volume names.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
TLO tracks inventory by visible volume name plus the path below the volume. It ignores and does not store the drive letter or WSL /mnt/<drive> prefix in bootlist.csv or the top SEARCH_PATH log headers. For example, [Backup-1]/mnt/e/Music and [Backup-1]/mnt/n/Music are treated as the same stored root [Backup-1] /Music when they refer to the same labeled volume.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
If no bracketed volume name is supplied, TLO substitutes the operating-system volume label for logging and existing-volume comparison when that label can be resolved. The default Windows-style labels New Volume and Local Disk are treated as blank rather than as useful volume names.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
If an explicit bracketed volume name is supplied, it must match the mounted drive label when that label can be resolved. A mismatch raises an alert and that path is not processed.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
For a labeled drive, TLO no longer asks whether to skip or re-inventory when it sees the same volume again. It applies the path relationship automatically: same path or parent path replaces that scope; child path replaces only entries below that child path; non-overlapping paths on the same volume are added to the same volume log header and appended.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Explicit [] means an explicit blank volume. It is rejected when the mounted drive has a nonblank, non-default operating-system volume label.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
For drives with a blank volume label, or with the default labels New Volume or Local Disk, TLO uses one append-only blank-volume log set. The log header is SEARCH_PATH: [] with no path. There is no skip or re-inventory for blank/default-label drives, so you must avoid or clean up duplicates yourself if the same blank/default-label drive content is scanned multiple times.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
When more than one path is queued, TLO uses the resolved volume name to schedule the searches. All paths with a blank volume name form one group and run one at a time in drive-letter order. Each named volume forms its own group; several paths on the same named volume run one at a time inside that group so their shared logs remain safe. According to Performance Mode and Max Workers, the blank-volume group and different named-volume groups can run at the same time.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
A single labeled volume log can list multiple SEARCH_PATH header lines when you add non-overlapping roots from the same drive over time.}
