\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Optional per-path directives can be added after the path. Use --$slam ARTIST_NAME to force an artist, --$copy DESTINATION to copy and tag that path's folders at the destination, or --$copy-delete DESTINATION to copy/move, verify when needed, delete the original, and tag the transferred folders. Legacy -$slam still works.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
The order of --$slam and the copy directive does not matter, but a single line cannot contain both --$copy and --$copy-delete. Destination folders must already exist and must be fully qualified paths.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Before inventory starts, TLO checks whether each copy destination has enough free space for the source root or roots assigned to it. If a destination is short on space, TLO stops and reports the destination, the affected source path or paths, and how much additional space is needed.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
When this capacity check is needed, the console first prints a Note explaining that TLO is checking source folder sizes before it checks destination capacity. Large roots can take a while to total, similar to opening folder Properties.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10152\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\intbl\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\loch
Volume label behavior: If no bracketed prefix is supplied, TLO uses the operating-system volume label for comparison and logging when available. Use [Volume] only when it matches the mounted drive label. Use [] only when an explicitly blank volume is intended and the mounted drive label is blank or unavailable.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

