8. Running the main GUI}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Start the Windows GUI with TLOHome/apps/Windows/tlo-ggi.exe, or the WSL/Linux GUI from TLOHome/apps/Linux. The GUI can also be preloaded with command-line arguments such as --myTLO, --TLOHome, --search-path, --compliant, --compliant-artist-mode master|as-is, --etree-lookup, --setlistfm-lookup, --performance-mode, and --max-workers. The main Inventory and Search windows no longer show an editable TLOHome box; the startup value is used for the whole session.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
On native Windows installations, drag a folder from File Explorer and drop it onto the Search Path text box. The dropped folder replaces the Search Path value. If a file is dropped, TLO uses the containing folder.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The GUI and CLI share the same defaults through the internal option registry. setlist.fm still depends on etreeDB: command-line startup rejects --setlistfm-lookup unless --etree-lookup is also supplied, and the GUI automatically selects etreeDB when setlist.fm is selected.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
When you click Inventory, the Inventory button should gray out immediately, the mutually exclusive Tag and Add Shows buttons should be disabled, and the output pane should show that the inventory request was accepted while TLO prepares the roots. If existing logs overlap the queued roots, TLO may show the Skip/Re-inventory prompt after this startup begins.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
If you click Quit while a full inventory scan is active, TLO immediately warns that it will take a moment to clean up before exiting, then stops active workers and removes active run logs.}
