\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
String1 Date: fallback when no String2 exists; show name becomes Artist Date. It uses the same Master or As-Is artist choice selected for the compliant run.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Standard video wrapper folders such as VIDEO_TS or BDMV can resolve from parent path components.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
The Billboard MP3 year-folder special case applies only when all inventoried music files are .mp3, the folder name is a four-digit year from 1959 through 2005, and billboard appears somewhere in the path. The exported setlist filename for this special case uses the same four-digit year.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af12\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb200\sa0\keepn\cf18\f4\fs26\b\dbch\af9\sl240\slmult1{\loch
Non-compliant mode}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Use Non-compliant mode when folder names vary or contain partial/uncertain metadata. Non-compliant mode uses more evidence and tries to fill missing metadata without overwriting earlier trusted fields.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Reads FLAC ARTIST, ALBUMARTIST, ALBUM, and DATE tags before path artist fallback. Tag values containing unknown or track are treated as blank for artist purposes.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Searches folder and path text for artist, date, venue, and location clues, including known artist names and aliases.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Aggregates related wrapper/part folders such as CD1/CD2/CD3 under one logical show when appropriate.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Uses selected setlist header metadata for date, artist, venue, and location fallback before track names or hash/checksum sections.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
Uses eTreeDB and setlist.fm only when enabled, and only to fill blanks or report observations.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Commas in unnumbered song lists do not need to be followed by spaces; TLO treats \u8220\'93Song A,Song B,Song C\u8221\'94 the same as \u8220\'93Song A, Song B, Song C\u8221\'94 when the item count matches the audio files.}
\par \trowd\trqc\ltrrow\trkeep\trpaddft3\trpaddt0\trpaddfl3\trpaddl0\trpaddfb3\trpaddb0\trpaddfr3\trpaddr0\clpadft3\clpadt108\clpadfr3\clpadr108\clcbpat23\cellx10152\pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\intbl\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa20{\loch
Practical choice: When in doubt, start with non-compliant mode for mixed real-world collections. Use compliant mode when you deliberately organized the folders to match the supported naming patterns and want those names trusted.}\cell\row\pard \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af12\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f4\fs32\b\dbch\af9\sl240\slmult1{\loch
10. Online lookup options}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl252\slmult1\sb0\sa80{\loch
Online lookup is optional. It is used to fill missing venue/location fields after artist and a full yyyy-mm-dd date are known. Later sources do not overwrite nonblank metadata found earlier; non-equivalent disagreements are reported as observations in the summary log.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
etreeDB checkbox or --etree-lookup: uses eTreeDB first among online sources. When tagging is enabled, the same option can also allow a last-resort eTreeDB song-title lookup if local setlist titles are not usable.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
setlist.fm checkbox or --setlistfm-lookup: uses setlist.fm as a last resort only when etreeDB does not return usable venue/location data. On the command line, --setlistfm-lookup requires --etree-lookup. In the GUI, selecting setlist.fm automatically selects etreeDB. If the same lookup response already contains song rows, TLO may reuse those cached rows for tagging; it does not make a separate setlist.fm call just to find track titles.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
setlist.fm requires SETLISTFM_API_KEY in the environment.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
setlist.fm requests are rate-limited to one request every 600 milliseconds across local workers and capped at 1,400 calls per inventory run.}
\par \pard\plain \s76\loch\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa200\contextualspace{\listtext\pard\plain \rtlch\af12 \ltrch \u61623\'3f\tab}\ilvl0\ls1 \fi-360\li360\lin360\sl240\slmult1{\hich\af7\loch\f7\loch
For U.S. lookup results, show names use Artist Date Venue City StateCode. Non-U.S. results use Artist Date Venue City Country.}
\par \pard\plain \s90\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af8\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\li360\lin360\ri144\rin144\sb40\sa80\ltrpar\cf0\f8\fs17\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af13\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1\fi0\li360\lin360\ri144\rin144\sb60\sa120{\loch
Command-line examples:\line tlo-gi.exe --TLOHome C:\\TLOHome --etree-lookup\line python3 tlo-gi.py --TLOHome "$TLOHome" --compliant --compliant-artist-mode as-is --etree-lookup --setlistfm-lookup}
\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af12\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f4\fs32\b\dbch\af9\sl240\slmult1{\loch
11. Tagging functions}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The tagging window is used when you want TLO to write tags to audio files. Its window title bar reads TLO Tagger GUI v1.1 Build 325. Inside the window, the single bold heading is Traders Little Helper\u8482\'99 Tagger App; there is no second in-window version heading. The exact layout may vary slightly by platform, but the main choices and actions are the same.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
The tagger also creates CorruptFlacs.txt in TLOHome. If a FLAC file cannot be opened or written during tagging, TLO appends the complete file path to that file so bad FLACs can be reviewed separately from other tagging errors.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1\loch

\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af12\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f4\fs32\b\dbch\af9\pagebb\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa0{\loch
GitHub update checks and Auto update}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af12\afs26\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb200\sa0\keepn\cf18\f4\fs26\b\dbch\af9\sl240\slmult1{\loch
Build 325 / v1.1 behavior}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
TLO can check the public GitHub Releases page for newer builds. The Inventory GUI hamburger menu and the Search GUI hamburger menu include Check for updates and Auto update.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Check for updates compares the installed build with the latest release under onaracstlo-lab/TradersLittleOrganizer. If the release is newer, TLO downloads the best matching ZIP to your Downloads folder and shows the full downloaded path.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Auto update is a download-only startup check. When enabled, TLO writes update-settings.json under TLOHome. On later Inventory or Search app startup, TLO sets the Auto update checkmark and checks GitHub at most once per day.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
TLO does not install updates automatically. It does not unzip the file, run an installer, or replace files while the program is open. Close TLO before extracting or copying update files.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Normal releases include six platform ZIP assets: one complete ZIP and one executable-only update ZIP for Windows, Linux, and macOS. Update ZIP examples are TLO_V1.1Build325_update_Windows.zip, TLO_V1.1Build325_update_Linux.zip, and TLO_V1.1Build325_update_macOS.zip. These update ZIPs contain only application executables/scripts, scan receipts, README_UPDATE.txt, UPDATE_MANIFEST.json, and checksums.txt. They intentionally do not contain inventory data, setlists, logs, databases, staged folders, or other user-created output.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
Complete release ZIPs are platform-specific and labeled complete, for example TLO_V1.1Build325_complete_Windows.zip, TLO_V1.1Build325_complete_Linux.zip, or TLO_V1.1Build325_complete_macOS.zip. Use the matching complete ZIP for a new installation or when release notes say required support files changed. If no matching platform update ZIP is available, the updater prefers the matching platform complete ZIP before any generic fallback.}
\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af12\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f4\fs32\b\dbch\af9\sl240\slmult1\sb0\sa0{\loch
Build 324 Add Shows Tag in Place}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1{\loch
When Tag in Place is checked in the main Inventory GUI, Add Shows writes tags to accepted show folders during both the regular readyForXfer processing path and the duplicate-resolution path. The tag step runs after any Rename Compliantly action and after generated setlist preparation, but before the folder is moved into staged.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa200{\loch
Add Shows does not perform Tag Copy. If the Tag Copy checkbox is selected for the main GUI, Add Shows ignores Tag Copy so the updater does not create a second destination outside the readyForXfer, dups, and staged workflow. Tag in Place remains honored for Add Shows when selected.}
\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af12\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sl240\slmult1\keep\sb480\sa0\keepn\cf17\f4\fs32\b\dbch\af9{\loch
Build 325 GUI TLOHome resolution}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033{\loch
The Inventory GUI and Search GUI no longer include an editable TLOHome input box. Set TLOHome before launch by using --myTLO, --TLOHome, or the TLOHome environment variable.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033{\loch
Resolution order is unchanged: --myTLO wins first, --TLOHome is next, and the TLOHome environment variable is used last. The resolved folder is used for bootlist.csv, setlists, logs, TLO_DBs, FAQ, Tag, Add Shows, and update-settings.json for the entire session.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af12\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe1033\hich\af2\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar\cf0\f2\fs20\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af10\langfe1033\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa200\ltrpar{\loch
To change TLOHome, close the app and relaunch it with a different shortcut, command-line argument, or environment variable value.}
\par }